'''BuiltWith''' is an [[Internet]] services company based in [[Manly, New South Wales|Manly]], Australia, which launched in August, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/builtwith_technology_profiler.php|title=BuiltWith.com Technology Profiler Launches Today|access-date=2011-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110822035422/http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/builtwith_technology_profiler.php#|archive-date=2011-08-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> The goal of BuiltWith is to help web developers, researchers, and designers track what technologies are being used by other websites, which may help them to decide what technologies to implement themselves.{{cn|date=July 2018}}
==Internet trends== BuiltWith Trends<ref>{{cite web|url=http://trends.builtwith.com|title=BuiltWith Trends}}</ref> is a comprehensive resource of what technologies the web has been using since 2010, across the Internet's top one million most visited sites by traffic as ranked by [[Quantcast]].<ref>https://blog.builtwith.com/2011/10/20/builtwith-top-sites/</ref> Its data is often quoted in Internet media reports related to internet technology trends.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://searchengineland.com/has-facebook-become-the-master-key-to-unlocking-the-web-75139|title=Has Facebook Become The Master Key To Unlocking The Web?}}</ref>
In 2010, [[John Resig]] opened the [[JQuery]] 2010 Keynote with statistics provided by BuiltWith Trends.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://events.jquery.org/2010/boston/video/video.php?talk=john-resig|title=JQuery 2010 Keywnote|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815220219/http://events.jquery.org/2010/boston/video/video.php?talk=john-resig|archivedate=2011-08-15|df=}}</ref>
